cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of matching images from different modalities, specifically photographs of building interiors and their corresponding floorplans. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it involves image processing and recognition. The use of neural networks for this task also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions a large-scale dataset, which could indicate that it falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the problem of matching floorplans and photographs could also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) category.
